# Usage: prettier-plugin-gml [command] [options]
# Utilities for working with the GMLoop toolchain.
# Provides formatting, benchmarking, and manual data generation commands.
# Run with a command name to get started (e.g., 'format --help' for formatting
# options). Tip: passing only a file or directory path runs 'format' for that
# target.
# Options:
#   -V, --version                              Show CLI version information.
#   -h, --help                                 Show this help message.
# Commands:
#   format [options] [targetPath]              Format GameMaker Language files using the prettier plugin.
#   lint [options] [paths...]                  Lint GameMaker Language files using @gmloop/lint
#   fix [options] [projectPath]                Run project codemods, lint fixes, and formatting in sequence
#   generate-gml-identifiers [options]         Generate the gml-identifiers.json artefact from the GameMaker manual.
#   generate-quality-report [options]          Generate a quality report (tests, lint, coverage, duplicates) and detect regressions.
#   collect-stats [options]                    Collect project health statistics (build size, TODOs, etc.)
#   generate-feather-metadata [options]        Generate feather-metadata.json from the GameMaker manual.
#   prepare-hot-reload [options]               Inject the hot-reload runtime wrapper into the latest GameMaker HTML5 output.
#   refactor [options] [operation] [paths...]  Perform safe, project-wide code transformations
#   watch [options] [targetPath]               Watch GML source files and coordinate hot-reload pipeline actions
#   watch-status [options]                     Query the running watch command's status server for metrics and diagnostics
#   help [command]                             display help for command
